---
title: coset_fft_field (fulu-polynomial-commitments-sampling)
---
stateDiagram-v2
    direction TB

    [*] --> q_init : start
    q_init --> q_copy : vals = copy(vals)
    q_copy --> q_check_inv : check inv flag
    q_check_inv --> q_inv_path : inv == True
    q_check_inv --> q_fwd_path : inv == False
    q_inv_path --> q_inv_fft : result = fft_field(vals, roots_of_unity, inv=True)
    q_inv_fft --> q_inv_shift : result = shift_vals(result, shift_factor.inverse())
    q_inv_shift --> [*] : return result
    q_fwd_path --> q_fwd_shift : vals = shift_vals(vals, shift_factor)
    q_fwd_shift --> q_fwd_fft : result = fft_field(vals, roots_of_unity, inv=False)
    q_fwd_fft --> [*] : return result

    note right of q_check_inv
        INV: shift_factor = PRIMITIVE_ROOT_OF_UNITY
        INV: Forward coset FFT shifts then FFTs; inverse FFTs then unshifts
        INV: Coset avoids division by zero when dividing by vanishing polynomials
    end note
